{"title_page": "King of the Bhaca Nation", "text_new": "Below are the traditional chiefs and kings of [[Zelemu]] and Wushe people who were later referred to as [[AmaBhaca]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! King/\n! Reign\n|-\n| [[Lufulwenja]]\n| -\n|-\n| [[Zelemu]]\n| -\n|-\n| [[Wabana Lufulwenja|Wabana]]\n| \n|-\n| [[Wushe]]\n| \n|-\n| [[Vebi]]\n| \n|-\n| [[Mjoli]]\n| -\n|-\n| [[Khalimeshe]]\n| -\n|-\n| [[Madzikane]]\n| 1810-1824\n|-\n| [[Sonyangwe]]\n| 1824-1826\n|-\n| [[Ncapai]]\n| 1826-1845\n|-\n| [[Diko ka Ncapai]]\n| 1845-\n|-\n| [[Makaula]]\n| -\n|-\n| [[Mdutyana]]\n| -\n|-\n| [[Nomtsheketshe]]\n| -\n|-\n|}\n\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.bhaca.co.za Bhaca| AmaBhaca]\n\n{{Ethnic groups in South Africa}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in South Africa]]\n[[Category:19th-century monarchs in Africa]]\n[[Category:South African chiefs]]\n[[Category:Monarchies of South Africa]]\n\n{{SouthAfrica-bio-stub}}\n{{Africa-royal-stub}}\n", "text_old": "Below are the traditional chiefs and kings of [[Zelemu]] and Wushe people who were later referred to as [[AmaBhaca]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! King/\n! Reign\n|-\n| [[Lufulwenja]]\n| -\n|-\n| [[Zelemu]]\n| -\n|-\n| [[Wabana]]\n| \n|-\n| [[Wushe]]\n| \n|-\n| [[Vebi]]\n| \n|-\n| [[Mjoli]]\n| -\n|-\n| [[Khalimeshe]]\n| -\n|-\n| [[Madzikane]]\n| 1810-1824\n|-\n| [[Sonyangwe]]\n| 1824-1826\n|-\n| [[Ncapai]]\n| 1826-1845\n|-\n| [[Diko ka Ncapai]]\n| 1845-\n|-\n| [[Makaula]]\n| -\n|-\n| [[Mdutyana]]\n| -\n|-\n| [[Nomtsheketshe]]\n| -\n|-\n|}\n\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.bhaca.co.za Bhaca| AmaBhaca]\n\n{{Ethnic groups in South Africa}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in South Africa]]\n[[Category:19th-century monarchs in Africa]]\n[[Category:South African chiefs]]\n[[Category:Monarchies of South Africa]]\n\n{{SouthAfrica-bio-stub}}\n{{Africa-royal-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Leschnei", "label": "safe", "comment": "DisambiguateWabanatoWabana Lufulwenjausingpopups", "url_pag