{"title_page": "Genevi\u00e8ve Gambillon", "text_new": "{{short description|French cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Genevi\u00e8ve Gambillon\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Genevi\u00e8ve Gambillon\n| nickname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1951|6|30|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Hudimesnil]], [[France]]\n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| currentteam    = \n| discipline     = Road & track\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      =  World Champion x2<br />{{flagicon|FRA}} National Champion x22\n| updated        = \n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry | {{FRA}} }} \n{{MedalCompetition | [[UCI Road World Championships]]}} \n{{MedalGold | [[1972 UCI Road World Championships|Gap 1972]] | Road Race}}\n{{MedalGold | [[1974 UCI Road World Championships|Montreal 1974]] | Road Race}} \n}}\n\n'''Genevi\u00e8ve Gambillon''' (born 30 June 1951, [[Hudimesnil]], [[Manche]]) is a former French [[road bicycle racing|road bicycle racer]]. She became the women's [[UCI Road World Championships|Road World Champion]] in 1972 and again in 1974. She retired from competition in 1978 and became a nurse at the hospital in [[Granville, Manche|Granville]].\n\n== Palmar\u00e8s ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n;1969\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n;1970\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n;1971\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:2nd [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n;1972\n:[[File:MaillotMundial.PNG|20px]] [[UCI Road World Championships \u2013 Women's road race]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n;1973\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:3rd [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n;1974\n:[[File:MaillotMundial.PNG|20px]] [[UCI Road World Championships \u2013 Women's road race]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n;1975\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:2nd [[UCI Road World Championships \u2013 Women's road race]]\n:2nd Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n;1976\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n;1977\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*{{Cycling archives|28382}}\n\n{{UCI Road World Champions \u2013 Women's road race}}\n{{French National Road Race Championships (women) |state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gambillon, Genevieve}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:French female cyclists]]\n[[Category:UCI Road World Champions (women)]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Manche]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{France-cycling-bio-1950s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Genevi\u00e8ve Gambillon\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Genevi\u00e8ve Gambillon\n| nickname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1951|6|30|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Hudimesnil]], [[France]]\n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| currentteam    = \n| discipline     = Road & track\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      =  World Champion x2<br />{{flagicon|FRA}} National Champion x22\n| updated        = \n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry | {{FRA}} }} \n{{MedalCompetition | [[UCI Road World Championships]]}} \n{{MedalGold | [[1972 UCI Road World Championships|Gap 1972]] | Road Race}}\n{{MedalGold | [[1974 UCI Road World Championships|Montreal 1974]] | Road Race}} \n}}\n\n'''Genevi\u00e8ve Gambillon''' (born 30 June 1951, [[Hudimesnil]], [[Manche]]) is a former French [[road bicycle racing|road bicycle racer]]. She became the women's [[UCI Road World Championships|Road World Champion]] in 1972 and again in 1974. She retired from competition in 1978 and became a nurse at the hospital in [[Granville, Manche|Granville]].\n\n== Palmar\u00e8s ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n;1969\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n;1970\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n;1971\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:2nd [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n;1972\n:[[File:MaillotMundial.PNG|20px]] [[UCI Road World Championships \u2013 Women's road race]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n;1973\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:3rd [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n;1974\n:[[File:MaillotMundial.PNG|20px]] [[UCI Road World Championships \u2013 Women's road race]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n;1975\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] [[French National Road Race Championships]]\n:[[File:MaillotFra.PNG|20px|Maillot tricolore]] Pursuit, [[French National Track Championships]]\n:2nd [[UCI Road World Championships \u2013 Women's road race]]\n:2nd Sprint, [[French National Track Championships]]\n;1976\n:[[File:Maillo